snippet.textDisplay:
I loved this challenge!


Edit: Also, why do I feel like Niki is set in two modes— cool and warm tones OR anything opposite of Gabi. I noticed she always refers to Gabi for reference of who she is but I just think it shows who she’s not, or who she’s trying not to be. I understand, having a twin, it’s hard to figure out your sense of self (trust me, I know) but I just want to say that it’s okay to have similarities and trying to NOT be like Gabi so forcefully kind of makes it painfully obvious. For the category “Out Of Your Element”, she chooses something that is IN Gabi’s. Now I know, the house was there and the room was there but I feel like Niki tries to hate/avoid pink so much bc she thinks it’s “Gabi’s thing” when it’s just a color. Call me brutal but this is seen in other videos. Gabi is just doing her thing and Niki has to always mention Gabi somehow (Especially in those challengers where they make outfits/costumes themselves). I saw the video where Niki confessed to feeling like she’s in Gabi’s shadow and I get it, but this is not how you find a separate self from who you are in terms of Gabi.

(Jesus warning about HELL FIRE):

And if thy hand causes you to sin,

cut it off:

it is better for thee

to enter into life maimed,

than having two hands

to go into hell,

into the fire

that never shall be quenched:

Where their worm dieth not,

and the fire is not quenched.

(Mark 9:43-44).

***(Cut if off): Should be taken figuratively; it means to take whatever drastic action is necessary to avoid sin.

***The imagery of Hell (Frequently called gehenna) comes from a garbage dump outside the walls of Jerusalem. Jesus hearers were familiar with the smoldering fires that always burned there.

***(((Obedience))) and (((self-control))) are necessary to overcome sin.

***The longing of the disciples for greatness needed to be reshaped according to God's purposes.
